A WOMAN was left critically injured on Tuesday afternoon after she set herself alight outside a shop on Union Street in Randgate, Randfontein, west of Johannesburg.The incident took place outside liquor store in the area. ER24 paramedics were dispatched to the scene, where they found the woman was surrounded by several community members. ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said paramedics assessed the woman and found that she had sustained second degree burn wounds to her head, face and neck. Local residents saw the woman purchase petrol at a nearby filling station. She later poured the 2 litre bottle filled with petrol over herself, took a lighter and set herself alight. Occupants of a passing taxi saw what happened and the driver stopped. One of the passengers jumped out and used a fire extinguisher to douse the flames, Meiring said He said the woman was treated for her injuries and provided medication before she was transported to Leratong Provincial Hospital for further care. The same woman was seen by community members throughout the day asking for jobs in the Randgate area before the incident occurred.news@thenewage.co.zaCALLYN MARKS